customer and product analysis For this dataset, we don't have explicit customer demographics, so we'll focus on food preferences instead¶

In [20]:
# Analyze distribution of food categories
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.countplot(y='Category', data=retail_data, order=retail_data['Category'].value_counts().index)
plt.title('Count of Items by Category')
plt.xlabel('Count')
plt.ylabel('Category')
plt.show()

In [24]:
# Define the nutritional factors to analyze
nutritional_factors = ['Calories', 'Total Fat', 'Saturated Fat', 'Cholesterol', 'Sodium', 'Carbohydrates', 'Dietary Fiber', 'Sugars', 'Protein']
In [25]:
# Calculate the correlation matrix with numeric_only set to True
correlation_matrix = retail_data[nutritional_factors].corr(numeric_only=True)
In [26]:
# Visualize the correlation matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt='.2f')
plt.title('Correlation Matrix of Nutritional Factors')
plt.show()
